Initialize & build the model. Identify the points of improvement and implement the same. (20)¶

In [23]:
# Trying with different activation functions, epochs,
# optimizer and batch_size to see the convergance of training and validation set

## Tyring the Model with relu, adam, epochs=50, and batch_size=4
ann = tf.keras.models.Sequential()

# Input layer and the first hidden layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=10, activation='relu'))

# Second hidden layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=6, activation='relu'))

# Output layer
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=1, activation='sigmoid'))

ann.compile(optimizer = 'adam', loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])

y_train = np.asarray(y_train).astype(np.int)

# plotting the validation and training accuracy

history = ann.fit(X_train, y_train,validation_split = 0.1, epochs=50, batch_size=4)
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
plt.title('model accuracy')
plt.ylabel('accuracy')
plt.xlabel('epoch')
plt.legend(['train', 'val'], loc='upper left')
plt.show()

# plot validation and training loss

plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
plt.title('model loss')
plt.ylabel('loss')
plt.xlabel('epoch')
plt.legend(['train', 'val'], loc='upper left')
plt.show()

## Builing Model with LeakyReLU, adam, epochs=50, batch_size=4

ann1 = tf.keras.models.Sequential()

# Adding a ReLU layer
ann1.add(tf.keras.layers.LeakyReLU(alpha=0.05))

# Adding the input layer and the first hidden layer
ann1.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=10))

# The second hidden layer
ann1.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=6))

# The output layer
ann1.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=1, activation='sigmoid'))

# Compiling the ANN
ann1.compile(optimizer = 'adam', loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])

# Plotting validation and training accuracy

history = ann1.fit(X_train, y_train,validation_split = 0.1, epochs=50, batch_size=4)
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
plt.title('model accuracy')
plt.ylabel('accuracy')
plt.xlabel('epoch')
plt.legend(['train', 'val'], loc='upper left')
plt.show()

# Plotting validation and training loss

plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
plt.title('model loss')
plt.ylabel('loss')
plt.xlabel('epoch')
plt.legend(['train', 'val'], loc='upper left')
plt.show()
